    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a heavy emphasis on exploiting favorable matchups, headlined by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Kyle Tucker** (73.58). **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** finds himself in an ideal spot against the high xERA of R. L\u00f3pez, benefiting from a massive 19% SP skill advantage and strong platoon dynamics, while **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite anchor, projected to thrive despite a slight park penalty. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.68) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.92) also clear the 70-point threshold, with the latter seeing a significant 14% boost from park factors that elevate him into a must-start tier. **Nasim Nunez** (65.67) rounds out the high-confidence group; his speed remains vital to our strategy in the scarce SB category, and the matchup against R. L\u00f3pez provides a high-floor opportunity for him to contribute.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Nolan Schanuel** (53.27), who actually posted a higher daily efficiency score than **Liam Hicks** (52.73) and **Miguel Vargas** (52.97). Ultimately, **Nolan Schanuel** was relegated to the bench because the current lineup construction maximizes our platoon edges and power-speed upside elsewhere. We are also monitoring the risk associated with **Gunnar Henderson** (53.09) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (53.25); both face pitchers with high hold percentages for base runners, which limits their ceiling in the SB category. Despite these hurdles, **Marcell Ozuna** (57.96) remains a solid UTIL play, providing a stable floor that justifies his inclusion over the remaining bench depth of **Jacob Wilson**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Josh Jung**. We remain focused on the efficiency of these starts, ready to pivot to **Andy Pages**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Brady House**, or **Dominic Smith** if internal roster churn or injury news dictates a shift in our 5x5 strategy.",
